@startuml failsafe_to_diagnostic_state_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Fail-safe To Diagnostic State Signal Flow\n(Core fail-safe / warning path -> DCM diagnostic severity publication)

participant "Core / CoreState\nfail-safe context" as FailCtx #F4F7FB
participant "DCM\ndiagnostic communication owner" as DCM #E8F7E8
participant "Diagnostic state bus" as DiagBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / testers" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Diagnostic Inputs ==

FailCtx -> DCM : CoreState::warningPathStatus\nCore::failSafeMode\nboundaryAlive
DCM -> DCM : warningPathStatus = boundaryAlive ? value : 2
DCM -> DCM : failSafeMode = boundaryAlive ? value : 2
DCM -> DCM : diagnostic severity = deriveSystemSeverity(...)
note right of DCM
Representative inputs
- warningPathStatus
- failSafeMode
- boundaryAlive
end note

== Diagnostic Publish ==

DCM -> DiagBus : diagnostic state / reason /\nservice-severity publication
DCM -> Obs : diagnostic trace /\nservice response context
note right of DCM
Representative outputs
- derived diagnostic severity
- route / reason context
- visible diagnostic trace state
end note

note over FailCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Core fail-safe and warning-path state reach DCM
2. DCM normalizes degraded/boundary-broken cases
3. Diagnostic severity is derived from fail-safe context
4. Testers and observers see the corresponding diagnostic state
end note

@enduml
